==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Defeature
<hw>De*fea"ture</hw> <pr>(?; 135)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>desfaiture</ets> a killing, disguising, prop., an undoing. See
<er>Defeat</er>, and cf. <er>Disfeature</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Overthrow; defeat.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧Nothing but
loss in their <xex>defeature</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Beau. &
Fl.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Disfigurement; deformity.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
⟦ldquo⟧Strange <xex>defeatures</xex> in my face.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Defeatured</ent>⟦br⟧
